00:00:56.930 --> 00:01:01.280
So, before I begin, I wanted to
share with you that, formerly,

00:01:01.280 --> 00:01:04.519
I was a Naval officer
on a nuclear submarine

00:01:04.519 --> 00:01:08.290
and actually see some
parallels between life

00:01:08.290 --> 00:01:09.980
on a submarine and
a store listing,

00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:11.313
that I'd like to share with you.

00:01:13.880 --> 00:01:14.840
So, icons.

00:01:14.840 --> 00:01:15.540
Icons.

00:01:15.540 --> 00:01:17.210
They're everywhere.

00:01:17.210 --> 00:01:20.315
My submarine, for example,
in itself, was an icon.

00:01:20.315 --> 00:01:23.576
It represented strength
and deterrence.

00:01:23.576 --> 00:01:25.080
You should be asking
yourself, what

00:01:25.080 --> 00:01:27.480
does your icon say
about your app or game?

00:01:30.050 --> 00:01:32.250
It's the first thing
people see and it

00:01:32.250 --> 00:01:34.250
doesn't matter how great
your app or game is,

00:01:34.250 --> 00:01:37.490
if no one downloads it.

00:01:37.490 --> 00:01:41.410
An effective app icon,
app or game icon,

00:01:41.410 --> 00:01:44.296
serves as a quick
identifier for your app.

00:01:44.296 --> 00:01:46.330
And you should also think
about changing it up,

00:01:46.330 --> 00:01:49.280
seasonally or perhaps
around holiday specials.

00:01:52.490 --> 00:01:54.780
Next is your title.

00:01:54.780 --> 00:01:58.960
It's also one of the
first things people see.

00:01:58.960 --> 00:02:03.600
I can refer to my old submarine
as the USS West Virginia SSBN

00:02:03.600 --> 00:02:07.250
736 Gold, Group
10, or I could just

00:02:07.250 --> 00:02:11.310
refer to as the 736 Gold, which
is what most people called it.

00:02:11.310 --> 00:02:13.030
Similarly, with
your app, you want

00:02:13.030 --> 00:02:14.810
to keep it short and sweet.

00:02:14.810 --> 00:02:20.250
Does anyone see the play on
words in this game's title?

00:02:20.250 --> 00:02:22.690
You want to be thoughtful
about your brand

00:02:22.690 --> 00:02:25.370
and anticipate the future.

00:02:25.370 --> 00:02:27.300
For example, how a
version two look?

00:02:30.560 --> 00:02:33.356
Next are descriptions.

00:02:33.356 --> 00:02:36.970
You can imagine, on a submarine
descriptions are everywhere.

00:02:36.970 --> 00:02:41.179
But the last thing you want to
do is go into a radiation zone

00:02:41.179 --> 00:02:43.220
without wearing your
thermoluminescent dosimeter.

00:02:45.732 --> 00:02:49.000
In your app, you want your
description to be short

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:51.850
and you want to use bullets to
highlight your product offering

00:02:51.850 --> 00:02:56.390
and tell the user what your
app or game actually does.

00:02:56.390 --> 00:03:00.475
This is also a great place
to talk about what's new.

00:03:00.475 --> 00:03:03.100
On a submarine, you can
imagine, day in and day out you

00:03:03.100 --> 00:03:05.700
get bored with the same
food, eating the same thing

00:03:05.700 --> 00:03:07.519
100 days in a row.

00:03:07.519 --> 00:03:09.310
But on occasion, we
would hear that there's

00:03:09.310 --> 00:03:11.810
some new food coming and
we'd all get excited.

00:03:11.810 --> 00:03:14.320
And I distinctly
remember one year,

00:03:14.320 --> 00:03:16.846
sort of floating around at
400 feet below the surface,

00:03:16.846 --> 00:03:18.470
we actually had turkey
on Thanksgiving,

00:03:18.470 --> 00:03:19.460
believe it or not.

00:03:19.460 --> 00:03:20.450
So that was cool.

00:03:20.450 --> 00:03:22.220
We were excited
about what was new.

00:03:22.220 --> 00:03:25.060
Similarly, with your
Play Store listing,

00:03:25.060 --> 00:03:27.600
you could talk about a
potential UI redesign

00:03:27.600 --> 00:03:30.200
or now that you may
be supporting where.

00:03:33.540 --> 00:03:36.660
So this brings us to
store listing experiments.

00:03:36.660 --> 00:03:38.970
This allows you to test
different parts of your store

00:03:38.970 --> 00:03:40.750
listing page.

00:03:40.750 --> 00:03:42.950
There are several
things you can test--

00:03:42.950 --> 00:03:46.610
your icon, your featured
graphic, screenshots,

00:03:46.610 --> 00:03:49.876
your promotional video,
and your description,

00:03:49.876 --> 00:03:56.530
all to see how these assets may
improve your conversion rate.

00:03:56.530 --> 00:03:59.870
On a submarine, we tested
various approaches.

00:03:59.870 --> 00:04:02.180
Experiment A could have
been approaching a target

00:04:02.180 --> 00:04:04.820
from beneath, whereas
experiment B could've

00:04:04.820 --> 00:04:06.460
been approaching a
target from behind,

00:04:06.460 --> 00:04:08.030
through the [INAUDIBLE].

00:04:08.030 --> 00:04:09.720
We would then take
that data and decide,

00:04:09.720 --> 00:04:11.470
what's the best way
to approach or targets

00:04:11.470 --> 00:04:14.130
going forward, based
on their attributes?

00:04:14.130 --> 00:04:17.079
Similarly, with store
listing experiments,

00:04:17.079 --> 00:04:20.390
you can use data
instead of intuition

00:04:20.390 --> 00:04:23.250
to optimize a text and
graphics of your store listing.

00:04:26.070 --> 00:04:30.660
So you want to start
with testing icons.

00:04:30.660 --> 00:04:33.230
Icons can have the
greatest impact,

00:04:33.230 --> 00:04:36.860
either positive or
negative, on your installs.

00:04:36.860 --> 00:04:39.700
Test early.

00:04:39.700 --> 00:04:41.497
Second, you want to
have a question in mind

00:04:41.497 --> 00:04:42.330
when you're testing.

00:04:42.330 --> 00:04:44.420
You want to have an objective.

00:04:44.420 --> 00:04:48.160
For example, does artwork
visualizing game play drive

00:04:48.160 --> 00:04:50.270
more installs than
artwork that doesn't?

00:04:54.830 --> 00:04:56.370
So, best practices.

00:04:56.370 --> 00:04:58.645
Developers have been asking
us for best practices.

00:04:58.645 --> 00:05:01.020
We would like to share with
you some things that we think

00:05:01.020 --> 00:05:02.603
would help or that
you should consider

00:05:02.603 --> 00:05:05.260
when running your experiments.

00:05:05.260 --> 00:05:11.480
So first, as I mentioned
before, start with a hypothesis.

00:05:11.480 --> 00:05:13.070
Then you want to test it.

00:05:13.070 --> 00:05:17.380
You want to test one thing at
a time, you want to iterate,

00:05:17.380 --> 00:05:19.580
and you want to do
the test long enough

00:05:19.580 --> 00:05:21.640
to get statistical significance.

00:05:21.640 --> 00:05:24.035
You don't want to cut
the test off too short.

00:05:26.284 --> 00:05:28.200
And then, of course, you
want to pay attention

00:05:28.200 --> 00:05:29.824
to the banner in the
Dev console, which

00:05:29.824 --> 00:05:32.510
gives you your results.

00:05:32.510 --> 00:05:35.900
Probably most importantly,
you want to be bold.

00:05:35.900 --> 00:05:37.650
Minor little
adjustments probably

00:05:37.650 --> 00:05:41.120
will be inconclusive, so
make big, broad changes

00:05:41.120 --> 00:05:42.020
and test those.

00:05:44.750 --> 00:05:47.060
I'm going to walk you
through a few examples

00:05:47.060 --> 00:05:51.290
here from successful
game developers who

00:05:51.290 --> 00:05:52.980
used store listing experiments.

00:05:52.980 --> 00:05:57.830
For example, "Kongregate"
tested different icon art

00:05:57.830 --> 00:06:01.150
and they saw a 91%
increase in installs

00:06:01.150 --> 00:06:02.600
just by testing the icon.

00:06:05.580 --> 00:06:07.940
As you can see, "Rovio"
used three rounds

00:06:07.940 --> 00:06:12.230
of testing until they
found the optimal winner.

00:06:12.230 --> 00:06:14.420
This may have taken
them a little bit longer

00:06:14.420 --> 00:06:17.930
but it was completely worth
the investment as they're

00:06:17.930 --> 00:06:20.210
able to iterate and
incorporate their learnings,

00:06:20.210 --> 00:06:22.890
and they actually saw
a pretty good boost.

00:06:22.890 --> 00:06:25.450
Does anyone see which
icon, which variant,

00:06:25.450 --> 00:06:27.740
of which experiment
is the winner?

00:06:31.235 --> 00:06:31.735
All right.

00:06:34.970 --> 00:06:36.990
In contrast, here's
an experiment

00:06:36.990 --> 00:06:40.240
conducted on screen shots.

00:06:40.240 --> 00:06:42.460
"Dots," a game
developer-- they used

00:06:42.460 --> 00:06:46.020
a very measured and
controlled approach when

00:06:46.020 --> 00:06:47.920
testing their screen shots.

00:06:47.920 --> 00:06:51.960
So they held everything
constant except the illustration

00:06:51.960 --> 00:06:59.060
of the game play mechanics and
they also had a great result.

00:06:59.060 --> 00:07:01.480
That's all for store
listings and experiments.

